`Scanner.nextInt()` will explode if there&#39;s no integer ready to read from the console.

To get the behaviour you want, you should check if there&#39;s an integer ready to read *before* you attempt read it, and stop reading if there isn&#39;t one ready to read.

To do this, replace this:

```java
for (int i = 0; i &lt; n; i++) {
    arr[i] = sc.nextInt();
}
```
with
```java
int count = 0;
while (sc.hasNextInt()) {
    arr[count++] = sc.nextInt();
}
```

See [live demo][1] that produces your desired output.


  [1]: https://ideone.com/FSTmJW

